scene.message:
Maki: Everyone seems to be{nl}
looking out for me. I'm{nl}
perfectly fine, though.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Yamaoka always told me{nl}
to have pride, and never to{nl}
fawn over the powerful.{waitkey}So he used to say.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Gone from our town,{nl}
and carried off by Aki here{nl}
too...{wait_fr:32} and the Harem Queen,{nl}
no less.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: A woman's heart is a{nl}
difficult thing, isn't it,{nl}
{ctl0f:1}?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Playing the ruler in a{nl}
place like this... what am I{nl}
supposed to tell Naito?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Did Sonomura give up on{nl}
Naito, I wonder?{waitkey}{clearbox}Maybe she went and fell for{nl}
someone else...{wait_fr:32} heh, no way{nl}
that's it.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Turning people into{nl}
ornaments — it's like a{nl}
detective novel I once read.{waitkey}{clearbox}...{wait_fr:32}how enthralling... Oh,{nl}
do excuse me.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: It's the human heart{nl}
that's the difficult thing,{nl}
isn't it.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Hey, hey{wait_fr:32}, who do you{nl}
think's cooler, that guy{nl}
standing there or me?{waitkey}It's me, right? Right, right?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: So even that Kozai had{nl}
her insecurities, huh.{waitkey}{clearbox}Me? I'm perfect, so there's{nl}
no way I've got any of those~!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: That mole, what{nl}
happened with it...?{waitkey}{clearbox}Goes to show you shouldn't{nl}
take UV rays lightly!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: After living it up so{nl}
good, she cheekily makes up{nl}
with Naito in the end. Some{nl}
nerve.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: Better to find out{nl}
early than to go on thinking{nl}
you're friends without{nl}
realizing a thing.{waitkey}{ret}

Young Man: This is a painting{nl}
the Queen made! Amazing,{nl}
right?{waitkey}{clearbox}The Queen's got a gift for{nl}
painting, and above all she's{nl}
a beauty!{waitkey}{clearbox}Her moles have multiplied{nl}
lately, but...{wait_fr:32} ah, but but,{nl}
she's still a beauty, okay!{waitkey}{ret}

Young Man: This painting's no{nl}
good at all! No talent{nl}
whatsoever!{waitkey}{clearbox}Calling herself a Queen and{nl}
all — have some shame, is how{nl}
I feel!{waitkey}{ret}

There's a painting said to be{nl}
the Queen's work.{wait_fr:21}...The style{nl}
looks like something you've{nl}
seen somewhere before.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: ...{wait_fr:32}This painting...!{wait_fr:48}{nl}
This is a painting Chisato{nl}
made...!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Chisato — {wait_fr:21}Chisato{nl}
Kozai? I heard she went{nl}
missing!{waitkey}{clearbox}Kozai's painting is here, and{nl}
it's supposed to be the{nl}
Queen's painting...?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Why?{wait_fr:48} Does that mean{nl}
Chisato is being held by the{nl}
Harem Queen...?{wait_fr:32}{waitkey}{ret}
